Sentencas: A solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) requires an elevated operating temperature to achieve high oxygen ion conductivity and the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, at high operating temperatures above 800 degrees C, performance deteriorates due to the chemical reaction of the electrode and electrolyte materials at the interface.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, it is necessary to lower the operating temperature to the intermediate temperature regime while maintaining the high oxygen reduction reaction kinetics.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: One approach is adopting the composite cathode material such as La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-delta-gadolinium doped ceria (LSCF-GDC).
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the high temperature in the fabrication process results in non-conduction material of strontium zirconate (SrZrO3, SZO) layers at the cathode/electrolyte interface, which blocks oxygen ion conduction and degrades the fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By utilizing the novel flash light sintering process, which can be completed in a few seconds, high temperature fabrication issues are solved.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The surface microstructure and thickness of the composite electrode are inspected using a scanning electron microscope (FE-SEM).
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The secondary phase generation and chemical reaction are analyzed using XRD (X-ray diffraction), SEM-EDS, and TEM-EDS.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode supported LSCF-GDC cathode cells are measured from 600 degrees C to 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density at 750 degrees C of the novel flash light sintered LSCF-GDC composite cathode cell is 727.4 mW/cm2.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition to the utilization of high performing cathode structure, the flash light sintering process dramatically reduces the process time and suppresses the side reaction at the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Sub-second sintering process for La6Sr4Co2Fe8O3-δ-gadolinium doped ceria composite cathode via a flash light irradiation method for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells
